              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "UNFLD",
                "DIFFR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The  cross section was derived from the",
                " experimental  yield  curve   as   the   approximated",
                " solution by the photon difference method."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Correction for spontaneous fission rate of the sample",
                " was  done  simply by measuring the time during which",
                " the  mica  was  in  contact  with  the  sample,  and",
                " calculating  the  track-density  correction from the",
                " known spontaneous fission half-life."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The  errors  are the quadratic sums of the",
                " standard deviations resulting from  track  countings",
                " and  an  estimated  (near  20%)  uncertainty  in the",
                " bremsstrahlung spectrum."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The photofission  cross section of U-238 was measured",
                " in the 2.75 to 5.75  MeV  range.  Cross  section  as",
                " small as 2 * 10**(-11) barns were detected.  A shelf",
                " was observed which had been predicted  to  occur  in",
                " the   cross   section  owing  to  the  dominance  of",
                " radiative decay of levels in the second well of  the",
                " potential barrier of U-238."
              ]
            }
          ],
